arts.ttl: Lazio Hero Against Dynamo Kyiv Praises Team’s Bounce-Back Ability
arts.sum: Lazio enjoyed a dream start to their first UEFA Europa League campaign since 2022/23, strolling to a 3-0 win against Dynamo Kyiv in Hamburg. Boulaye Dia stole the show at the Volksparkstadion with a first-half brace to inspire the Biancocelesti to a much-needed victory. arts.sum: Lazio kicked off their Europa League campaign with a convincing 3-0 win over Dynamo Kyiv in Hamburg. Marco Baroni made eight changes to the starting lineup that fell short against Fiorentina last Sunday. Boulaye Dia led the line supported by Loum Tchaouna, Fisayo Dele-Bashiru and Pedro.
